Ask HN: Is anyone able to download their Twitter data at the moment?
text:
I have been trying to download my data but I get stuck at the e-mail verification step:

> Verify it’s you: Help us keep your data safe. To verify your identity, we need to send you a verification code to ***@gmail.com

Nothing arrives, I have been waiting for ~24 hours, tried 6+ times, checked on the spam folder. I also requested help from @Twitter and @TwitterSupport but they are not responding (I guess due to the massive lay-offs?).

Is anyone else having this problem?

text:

In your field which books do you think became popular for all the wrong reasons and set your field back in terms of preaching wrong practices?

Ask HN: Unsigned Software Downloads
text:
Why do some large, reputable open source projects not provide digital signatures for software downloads? I thought everyone did this now, but neither Golang or Postgres sign downloads they publish. Why not?

https://www.postgresql.org/ftp/source/v15.0/

https://go.dev/dl/

As counter examples, but the Linux kernel and rust sign downloads they publish:

https://forge.rust-lang.org/infra/other-installation-methods.html#source-code

https://kernel.org/

Tell HN: Sleeping in the Office
text:
Pre Covid, my boss disallowed remote work because someone used to sleep in the office

Some person had no home, and worked well, but slept at night in our office.

But my boss didn’t like it. Who would?

Life doesn’t make sense. So, he told his college kids to not work from home. It’s a play on words. Work is not home. Home is not work.

I had thought about it for so long.

Edit: Or is work home?

Confusion, how simple a phenomenon, is complicated.
